      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2018-02-15</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-05-08T13:54:07Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong></strong><b>Services, Tools, and Opportunities to Prevent Homelessness Act of 2018 or the STOP Homelessness Act of 2018</b></p> <p> This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) establish the Stop Homelessness Fund for the Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) to use to provide housing and services to homeless and formerly homeless individuals; (2) allow individual taxpayers to designate on their tax returns a portion (not less than $1) of any overpayment of tax or an additional contribution for the fund; (3) provide appropriations to the fund equal to twice the amount that is designated and contributed by taxpayers to the fund; and (4) require HUD to include in the President's budget, beginning with FY2019, a description of the uses of the fund during the previous fiscal year and the proposed uses for the next fiscal year.</p> <p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-02-15T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
